---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How many bushels per hour do you roast?",
    answer: `Moisture makes a big difference. Dry beans go faster than wet beans. Estimated rates for soybeans:<br/><br/>
    <strong>10%</strong> = 350+ bu/hr<br/>
    <strong>12%</strong> = 320 bu/hr<br/>
    <strong>14%</strong> = 300 bu/hr<br/>
    <strong>16%</strong> = 260 bu/hr<br/>
    <strong>18%</strong> = 220 bu/hr<br/>
    Over 18% the rate holds steady but temperature begins to fall.`
  },
  {
    question: "What do I need to supply?",
    answer: "We come ready to work! LP gas and electricity are on the service truck. We have an inbound roaster feed auger and a boom auger discharge. Most trucks and wagons can be unloaded and filled. You supply the grain and someone to move trucks and wagons and shovel out grain bins."
  },
  {
    question: "How wet can soybeans be roasted?",
    answer: "We achieve high bypass protein levels with beans up to 18% moisture — no problem. We can roast up to 25% moisture beans. Extremely wet beans will be roasted, dried, and storable with reduced trypsin inhibitor and increased bypass values. They may not hit optimum 60%+ bypass, but roasting is a great alternative to giving them away at the elevator after all the shrinks and docks."
  },
  {
    question: "What is the shrink on roasted soybeans?",
    answer: "The only shrink is water removed by the process. Ending moisture is usually about 3–4%. A 13% soybean will have about 9% moisture shrink and nearly zero dry matter shrink. Our on-site service keeps your dry matter tonnage in your inventory — most farmers see 10% or more dry matter loss when roasting at the co-op."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I fill a grain bin with roasted soybeans?",
    answer: "Yes. If you have a fan on the bin, we can fill it with fresh roasted soybeans. We routinely fill 10,000–20,000 bushel bins."
  },
  {
    question: "How long can I store roasted soybeans?",
    answer: "A long time! Most customers roast annually. Through the years we've seen 5 and 6 year old roasted soybeans fed with no herd performance loss."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you only roast during harvest?",
    answer: "No. We roast for our customers all year round."
  },
  {
    question: "I don't have a bin. Can I still roast?",
    answer: "Yes! Many customers roast from wagon to wagon after harvest and store roasted soybeans on the wagon until fed. Others lay a few thousand bushels in a commodity shed."
  },
];
---

<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-tag">Common Questions</p>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
      {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="faq-question">{faq.question}</span>
            <span class="faq-chevron">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" width="20" height="20"><path d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-answer" set:html={faq.answer} />
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq {
    padding: 7rem 2rem;
    background: white;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section-tag {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--color-rust);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    color: var(--color-earth);
  }

  .faq-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }

  .faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }

  summary {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-question {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-earth);
  }

  .faq-chevron {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--color-gray);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-item[open] .faq-chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .faq-answer {
    padding: 0 0 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 90%;
  }
</style>
